title: All for One
description: Pocoyo wants to play but Baby Bird is flying up in the sky, Pato and Octopus are helicoptering, Elly is jumping up into outer space and even little Caterpillar transforms into a butterfly and flutters away. Pocoyo feels left out so they get together to help him fly up in the sky along with them.

title: Super Pocoyo
description: Today Pocoyo is Super Pocoyo - a superhero determined to rescue his friends from tight fixes - even when they don't need to be rescued.

title: Twinkle, Twinkle, Little Star
description: Come along and sing with Pocoyo and his friends to Twinkle, Twinkle, Little Star!

title: Remember When…
description: Pocoyo want to show his friends a film of all his favourite memories. His friends are bored and a bit miffed when they realise they don't feature in the movie at all. So Pocoyo shows them some more favourite bits, this time featuring Elly, Pato and the others, all in embarrassing, funny, silly fixes. Pocoyo thinks it's hilarious but of course his friends are hurt. So Elly shows her favourite bits: all of her bits show her being beautiful, graceful and strong. Pato doesn't like her bits so he shows his. Again, the others get bored and unhappy. They all argue about who should show clips till Baby Bird brings along a selection of clips of everyone having fun together. Those are the best bits of all!

title: Elly Spots
description: Elly is stricken with a case of the Elly Spots, and Pato and Pocoyo have to forsake their picnic to look after her. Once she is better, she makes it up to them.

title: Swept Away
description: Pocoyo shows us that tidying can be fun too: a broom can be a horse, a guitar, or even a hockey stick!

title: Bedtime
description: It's Pocoyo and Pato's bedtime but Pocoyo isn't tired. Every time Pato is just about to fall asleep, he is disturbed by Pocoyo. Eventually Pocoyo is tired out too and together we help Pato drift off to sleep at last.

title: Finger Family
description: Come along and sing with Pocoyo and his friends to the Finger Family song!

title: Paint Me a Picture!
description: Pocoyo has decided to paint a portrait. But none of his friends will sit still long enough for him to be able to finish his picture. Pocoyo is sad because he feels like he hasn't managed to do what he set out to do - but looking at his picture with fresh eyes he sees that his picture really does capture the true essence of his friends.

title: Happy Birthday
description: Come along and sing Happy Birthday to celebrate a birthday with Pocoyo and his friends!

title: Elly's Shoes
description: Elly gets a fancy new pair of dressing up shoes. She loves wearing them so much that she won't take them off, even to go to bed!

title: Elly on Ice
description: Pocoyo and Pato are having fun ice-skating. Elly is a great dancer and wants to have a go, but every time she tries she falls over flat on her bottom. Even Whale and Octopus put on a great duet ice-skating routine. Poor Elly is about to give up. But we encourage her to have another go, and Pocoyo and Pato help her to get started. Gradually she gets the hang of it and her confidence increases till she performs an amazing routine and achieves the highest score of the day.

title: Don't Touch!
description: Pocoyo is left in charge of guarding the beautiful castle Elly has built from blocks. Soon Pocoyo can't resist the temptation to touch the castle, and the whole thing comes tumbling down. How can Pocoyo make it up to Elly?

title: Mr. Pato
description: Come along and sing Mr Pato with Pocoyo and his friends!

title: Camping
description: Pocoyo, Pato and Elly are preparing to go camping. When night falls they begin to play by scaring each other, but what started as a game becomes much more real as they head to bed and everyone is scared by a mysterious noise. In the morning they laughingly discover that the terrifying noise was just the snores of Sleepy Bird.

title: Choo Choo Wa
description: Come along and sing Choo Choo Wa with Pocoyo and his friends!

title: Ring a ring a potato
description: Come along and sing Once I caught a Fish Alive with Pocoyo and his friends!

title: Angry Alien
description: An angry alien finds his way to Pocoyo's world and declares that he wants to be king. Pocoyo, Elly and Caterpillar are all friendly but the alien just bosses them around and tries to scare them. When the alien tells Pato what to do, Pato finds it rather helpful. This goes against what the alien was expecting. Finally the alien is upset because he's not getting the reaction he wanted. He sobs and sobs. Pocoyo et al are concerned and kind. The alien realizes that he is likable, and if he'd just stop being so angry, he could have fun.

title: Mystery Footprints
description: Pocoyo and his friends are learning about the different tracks different feet - and paws - make on the ground. When they see some huge footprints they are scared until they realize that one of them is wearing some rather unusual footwear…

title: Magic Act
description: Pocoyo is doing a magic show. He expects everyone to watch very carefully and take him very seriously but unfortunately his tricks don't quite go to plan and his friends all laugh. They're really enjoying the show. They think Pocoyo is great at being a funny magician. But that's not what Pocoyo wants to be - he wants to be taken very seriously - so he goes off in a huff. In the meantime, Pato, Elly and Baby Bird go around Pocoyo-land to tell everyone about the magnificent hilarious magician whose show they enjoy so much. As Pocoyo sulks, his friends gather around him, excited to see his tricks. Pocoyo is overwhelmed that his friends liked his show so much. He does some more tricks and his friends are thrilled.

title: Magical Watering Can
description: Pocoyo gives the last drop of water from his watering can to his friends instead of using it to water his musical flowers. Pato and Elly are grateful, so they re-pay the favor.

title: A Present for Elly
description: Pocoyo decides to make a very special birthday present for Elly. Can you guess what it is?

title: Sleepy Bird's Surprise
description: Sleepy Bird's egg takes on a life of its own. Pocoyo and Pato have to get it back to the nest - just in time for it to hatch.

title: The Great Race
description: Elly and Pocoyo have a race, and are surprised when an outsider narrowly beats them.

title: A Very Special Guest
description: It's Christmas and Pocoyo and friends are preparing to celebrate at Elly's house. Elly, Pato, Baby Bird and Caterpillar are in charge of decorations and dinner, while Pocoyo and Loula fetch a tree. Everything is going well until Pocoyo and Loula bring the tree, along with an unexpected guest: a huge yeti! Elly, Pato, Baby Bird and Caterpillar are very scared, so Pocoyo will have to show them that there is always space for one more at the table for Christmas dinner. Will they be able to enjoy it?

title: Talent Show
description: It's the day of the Talent Show. First Elly does some ballet karate. Then it's Baby Bird's turn: he's a crazy pinball wizard. Caterpillar nervously says she'll have her go later. Whale sings down the line from underwater. Pato does some unbelievable impersonations. Pocoyo reads out a story he's written. It's Caterpillar's turn but she's too scared. She doesn't want to do her bit. She's shy. We persuade her to show us her talent. She does a talk all about hippopotami. Once she's started, there's no stopping her. It's wonderful. What a fantastic and unforgettable display of unique talents. Everyone can do something special.

title: Crazy Inventions
description: Pocoyo the super inventor has a lab full of hare-brained inventions. His helper Pato volunteers to test out his new time machine, but things don't go quite to plan and Pocoyo will travel through the third dimension to rescue his friend.

title: Dirty Dog
description: Pato is enjoying watering his flowers when all of a sudden he notices that something smells horrible. It's Loula: she stinks. Elly is putting on perfume, and she too notices how bad Loula smells. Pooey! When Pocoyo can't eat his sandwich because Loula smells so bad, he makes a plan. Loula needs a wash. The only problem is, Loula doesn't want to get in the bath and gives chase to Pocoyo, Elly and Pato. Pocoyo and his friends decide to trick Loula into a cleaning machine but their plan is thwarted. However will they stop the smell? Then, all of a sudden it begins to rain and Loula finally gets her long-awaited clean.

title: Drummer Boy
description: Pocoyo wants to drum, but his friends are all busy playing different things. Pocoyo learns that sometimes his friends don't want to do exactly the same things as him.

title: Tea time
description: Come along and sing with Pocoyo and his friends to Tea Time!

title: Pocoyo Gets it Right
description: Pocoyo wants to play 'pitch and putt' like his friends, Pocoyo and Elly, but he can't quite get the hang of it. He watches carefully and finally grasps where he was going wrong.

title: Baa Baa Black Sheep
description: Come along and sing Baa Baa Black Sheep with Pocoyo and his friends!

title: Picnic
description: Pocoyo, Pato and Elly go on a picnic. Soon the sandwiches they have in their basket begin to move all by themselves and escape. The three friends pursue the sandwiches until they are finally able to trap them. At the end of the episode Pocoyo, using a magnifying glass, discovers that ants were attempting to take the sandwiches and invites them to the picnic.

title: Having a Ball
description: Pocoyo and Pato are enjoying playing with their new ball. But all of a sudden, the ball takes on a life of its own, and Pocoyo and Pato have to chase it. Who's got the ball…? It's Baby Bird who just wants to play too!

title: Ten in the Bed
description: Come along and sing with Pocoyo and his friends to Ten in the Bed!

title: Let's Go Camping!
description: A camping trip is planned - but Pocoyo and Pato have too much luggage. In the end they realize that all you really need for a nice camping trip are your friends - and then it doesn't really matter whether you're at home or away.

title: Shutterbug
description: Pocoyo, Elly and Baby Bird are bored of Pato's countless flower photos so they encourage him to take pictures of them instead. But each time Pato takes a photo, someone moves. Pato is exasperated because he wants to take perfect portraits but there's always something not quite right. Pato gives up. His friends put on an exhibition of his photos to show him that his pictures may not be exactly what he had in mind, but they really are wonderful because they capture the fun the friends have together.

title: Not in My Backyard
description: Pocoyo discovers some old rubbish and decides to have a clear out. Baby Bird, Pato and Elly do the same. Soon there's a huge pile of rubbish, and it turns out it's on Caterpillar's doorstep. The rubbish keeps getting thrown around until finally Pocoyo follows the rubbish and realizes it's just going in a circle. In order to break the cycle, Pocoyo helps his friends make some new fun toys and games out of the rubbish.

title: Pocoyo's Band
description: Pocoyo finds a box full of musical instruments. When he learns how to use them, he calls on his friends to form a rock band. At first the band is a disaster, but in the end they learn to play together and are able to make some great music.

title: Space Christmas
description: It's Christmas and Angry Alien, who hates this holiday, is preparing to spend the evening all by himself, with no celebrations... until Pocoyo and friends turn up at his house to keep him company. How is he going to like Christmas with no decorations, carols or friends? But they're here to solve that! Angry Alien will try everything he can to stop them from making this a great Christmas. Will he succeed?

title: Pato's Postal Service
description: When Pocoyo wants to send a letter to Elly, Pato embraces the very important role of postman. After much to-ing and fro-ing, Pato delivers a mammoth package!

title: Humpty Dumpty
description: Come along and sing Humpty Dumpty with Pocoyo and his friends!

title: Vamoosh on the Loosh
description: Pocoyo promises to teach Baby Bird to drive the Vamoosh but keeps putting it off. Fed up, Baby Bird decides to have a go on his own but he doesn't know how. The Vamoosh spins out of control. Pocoyo realises he must keep to his promise and teach Baby Bird to drive properly.

title: The ABC Song
description: Come along and sing with Pocoyo and his friends to The ABC Song!

title: Baby Bird Bother
description: Baby Bird is in awe of Pocoyo as he plays skillfully with a bouncy ball. Baby Bird continues to admire Pocoyo but this time it's his construction skills as Pocoyo plays with his blocks. And yes, Baby Bird thinks Pocoyo is the best at painting too. At first Pocoyo thinks it's great to have an admirer but soon, Pocoyo can't do anything without Baby Bird interrupting. Eventually Pocoyo gets so frustrated that he sends Baby Bird away. Pocoyo enjoys doing everything all by himself but it's not long before he wonders where his friend Baby Bird has gone. When Pocoyo realizes that Baby Bird was only trying to be his friend Pocoyo decides to invite Baby Bird to a party especially for him.

title: Elly's Big Chase
description: Elly inadvertently sets off on a fantastic journey - all the while fast asleep on her chair - as Pocoyo and Pato protect her from danger.

title: Johny Johnny Yes Papa
description: Come along and sing with Pocoyo and his friends to Johnny Johnny yes papa!

title: We Wish You a Merry Christmas
description: Come along and sing We Wish you a Merry Christmas this festive season with Pocoyo and his friends! Merry Christmas!

title: See My Little Hand
description: Come along and sing See my Little Hand with Pocoyo and his friends!

title: Elly's Doll
description: Pocoyo is charged with looking after Elly's favorite doll, but he breaks it. Instead of telling her the truth, he pretends to be the doll. It's only when nature gets the better of Pocoyo that Elly realizes what's going on. She forgives Pocoyo warmly and mends her doll.

title: Once I caught a Fish Alive
description: Come along and sing Once I caught a Fish Alive with Pocoyo and his friends!

title: Get Lost Loula
description: Let's play Hide and Seek! Pocoyo is the seeker and is brilliant at it - but only thanks to Loula. When Loula gets all the praise for being a super-seeker, Pocoyo is jealous. He throws a ball very far away to make Loula run off and chase it. His friends think it was a nasty thing to do and so Pocoyo feels bad and decides he must now find Loula. They follow her footprints but she's gone really far and they just can't find her anywhere. Finally at an island in the sea they despair: they think she's gone forever. But we can already see that Loula is safe and sound. Everyone is reunited and Pocoyo can celebrate being a super-seeker too, after all.

title: Giggle Bug
description: When Pocoyo is down in the dumps, Octopus cheers him up. Elly falls over doing her latest dance routine and Octopus cheers her up too. Finally Pato is in a bad mood, and Octopus has to work really hard to get him to giggle.

title: Guess What?
description: Pocoyo plays a game with us. He shows us a series of different extremely strange shapes and wants us to guess what they are. A fun guessing game, learning to look at things in different ways...

title: The Day of the Dead
description: Pato misses his Grandfather and decides to honor his memory on Day of the Dead by making a shrine with his photograph and the things he liked the most. Pocoyo and friends will help him to set it up to try cheer up Pato.

title: Boo Boo Song
description: Come along and sing the Boo Boo song with Pocoyo and his friends!

title: A Little Something Between Friends
description: Pocoyo and Pato fall out - really fall out. They are so angry with each other that they build a wall between themselves. They each sit sulking on either side of the wall, until gradually they realize that it's no fun being angry with your friend, and actually they miss each other.

title: Keep Going Pocoyo
description: Pato and Elly are enjoying skipping with a skipping rope. Pocoyo thinks it looks like fun and he wants to skip too. Try as he might though, Pocoyo can't do it. So he asks his friends for help.

title: Scooter Madness
description: Pocoyo and Pato find Elly's scooter and decide to take it back to her. Pato enjoys showing off his scooter skills and quickly forgets who it belongs to. Pato's scooter tricks get bigger and bigger until eventually he breaks the scooter into pieces. Pocoyo and Pato try to fix the scooter but it's no good. However will they tell Elly? At first they try to cover up what they've done but eventually they have to confess. Thankfully Elly is not upset with them as she has another scooter and is just pleased her friends told the truth in the end.

title: Upside Down
description: Pato gets stuck hanging upside down from the sky. Pocoyo and the friends try to help him down.

title: The Big Sneeze
description: Elly has a cold and her huge trumpeting sneezes keep knocking Pocoyo's tower of bricks down. Pocoyo and Pato have to work out what to do.

title: Scary Noises
description: Pocoyo and Pato are out for an adventure in the Vamoosh but have to land on a strange planet when a part of the Vamoosh falls off. Whilst searching for the missing part, Pato gets scared because he hears a strange, scary noise. They both realize there is nothing to be scared of and the alien just wants to make friends.

title: Mr Big Duck
description: Pato is enjoying playing at being very grown up and doesn't want to join in the games with his friends. Eventually though, Pato and the others realize that playing with friends is much more fun than hanging around being 'cool'.

title: Ready, Steady, Go!
description: Pocoyo, Pato and Elly challenge each other to a race. Everything starts out well, but becomes more complicated as everyone begins to cheat so that they will arrive in first place. After various unexpected events everyone learns that winning isn't the most important and that it is more important to enjoy oneself.

title: Hockey Pockey
description: Come along and sing the Hockey Pockey with Pocoyo and his friends!

title: Big Scary Slide
description: There's lots of new exciting playground rides in Pocoyoland including one huge daring slide. Pocoyo is too scared to give it a go. Pocoyo bravely helps his friend and overcomes his fear.

title: The Finger Family
description: Come along and sing with Pocoyo and his friends to the Finger Family song!

title: Color My World
description: Pocoyo finds a new toy - a remote control that changes the colors of the things around him. It's great fun until he changes the colors of his friends. We have to help him put things back to the way they were.

title: Pato's Egg
description: Pato finds an egg and immediately falls in love with it: he wants to take care of the little baby inside the egg. When the egg hatches he gets the shock of his life: it's not a cute little duckling at all, but a very odd looking spider. His friends are terrified of the little creature and won't play with Pato if he brings it along. Pato rather craftily and meanly makes the little spider go away and do things on its own, so Pato can play with Pocoyo and Elly. Finally the little spider makes their hearts melt when he shows them that there's nothing to be scared of and he just wants to be their friend.

title: Guess the fruit
description: Come along and sing the Yes Yes Vegetable Song with Pocoyo and his friends!

title: The Key to it All
description: Pocoyo finds a key which leads him on an exciting and magical adventure of exploration and discovery.

title: Invisible Pocoyo
description: Pocoyo finds a fantastic new toy: a machine that makes things invisible! He wants to show his friends his exciting discovery but they are too busy doing their own thing. Pocoyo is miffed but then realizes that he can have some fun with them, without them knowing about it. He makes himself invisible and starts to undertake various sneaky antics which utterly dumbfound his pals. Things get out of hand when Pato blames Elly and Elly blames Pato - even though we all know it's really Pocoyo's fault. Finally the truth is revealed when Baby Bird presses the button on the machine and Pocoyo is de-invisible-ised! In the end, they all play at being invisible together.

title: Lula
description: Come along and sing the song Lula with Pocoyo and his friends!

title: Elly's Tea Party
description: Elly invites her chums to a tea party but they don't want to come because they know how bossy Elly is at her tea parties. The tea parties are no fun because Elly is always barking out rules and orders. But when Pocoyo and Pato smell Elly's gorgeous biscuits, they realize what they're missing out on and they change their minds. They really want to go to her tea party now. Before they can dig into the biscuits though, Elly bosses them around. Pocoyo and Pato are exasperated and leave Elly to it. Elly realizes that her friends are sad, and a tea party isn't really a tea party unless you've got friends there with you. So Elly stops being bossy, and they all have a fun party eating the treats together.

title: Egg Surprises (The Farm)
description: Come along and sing Egg Surprises (the farm) with Pocoyo and his friends!

title: Double Trouble
description: Pocoyo wants to play ball but Pato is stubborn: he wants to play on the see-saw. Elly turns up so Pocoyo goes to play catch with her. Pato's left on his own. And the see-saw is no fun on your own. But he has an idea. He gets a machine and makes a copy of himself, a clone. The clone likes playing for a while but when they both want to play with the same toy car, they fall out. So Pato makes another Pato. Every time he makes a new Pato, something goes wrong, because the Patos all want the same thing and are as stubborn as each other. Finally, one of the clone Patos clones itself and soon there are crowds of Patos rampaging all around the place. Pocoyo and Elly to the rescue! They turn off the machine and all the copy Patos disappear. Phewy. To end, Pato plays ball.

title: Little Bird and Sleepy Bird
description: Come along and sing Little Bird and Sleepy Bird with Pocoyo and his friends!

title: Pocoyo and the Haunted House
description: In this spooky episode, Pocoyo and Pato go trick and treat and visit a haunted house with all sorts of frights and jokes, where nothing is what it looks like.

title: Move Your Body
description: Come along and sing Move Your Body with Pocoyo and his friends!

title: Pocoyo's Scary Halloween
description: It's Halloween and Pocoyo and friends are working on their costumes. Pocoyo is excited because he has prepared a surprise - he has hired Chihuahua Brothers to scare his friends! Who will scare who?

title: My Pato
description: Pato and Elly are arguing over their blocks when Caterpillar and Baby Bird walk past with presents for Pato. Oh no! Pocoyo and Elly have forgotten Pato's birthday. Elly is quick to whisk Pato off to a birthday picnic, determined to prove how much she cares. Not to be outdone, quick-thinking Pocoyo appears at the picnic with a present but Elly retaliates and 'accidentally' breaks it. Pocoyo and Elly fight so hard over Pato that he's almost broken in two. Fed up with all the fight Pato packs his things and is about to leave. When Pocoyo and Elly realize that their fighting has driven Pato away, they quickly make up and turn their efforts into making a special birthday party for Pato.

title: Five Little Birds
description: Come along and sing Five Little Birds with Pocoyo and his friends!

title: Fruit Cake
description: Come along and sing Fruit Cake with Pocoyo and his friends!

title: A Dog's Life
description: Pocoyo pretends to be an elephant, a duck and a dog - but when Loula needs his help, Pocoyo sees that sometimes it's best just to be himself.

title: Hush
description: Pocoyo and his gang want to make friends with a butterfly but every time they say hello, it flies away. With Sleepy Bird's help, they realize how to get close to the butterfly.

title: Pocoyo, Pocoyo
description: Pocoyo discovers a fabulous new playmate - his echoooo-ooo-ooo-ooo!

title: Sneaky Shoes
description: Pato, Pocoyo and Elly are having fun doing running and jumping competitions: except Pato is taking it very seriously. So when he loses he's mighty miffed. He is a very bad loser. He goes off in a huff and finds some swanky sneakers. He tries them on and discovers that these are no ordinary sneakers: they have a life of their own, they have super powers. Once he's mastered them he challenges Pocoyo and Elly to a re-match. Of course now he wins the running and jumping contests hands down. But Elly feels that something's up and doesn't want to compete anymore. When Pato tries to take the shoes off he realizes they won't undo. He's stuck and the shoes are going crazy. Luckily Caterpillar and Baby Bird save the day by getting the shoes off. And Pato has learnt that cheating just isn't a good way to win.

title: A Ram Sam Sam
description: Come along and sing A Ram Sam Sam with Pocoyo and his friends!

title: His name is Pato
description: Come along and sing His Name is Pato with Pocoyo and his friends!

title: Sleepy bird is sleepy
description: Come along and sing with Pocoyo and his friends to Sleepy bird is sleepy!

title: Pato's Paintings
description: Everyone's preparing for a painting exhibition. Everyone except Pato who says he's not bothered about painting. When the show opens, Pato unexpectedly exhibits his paintings: they are amazing masterpieces (Actually they are real masterpieces. He didn't paint them!). Everyone is very impressed and asks him to paint another. But he can't, because in fact he cheated: he didn't paint these pictures at all. Pocoyo and the audience encourage Pato to have a go at painting. He paints a beautiful flower and feels very pleased with himself. His painting takes its place in the exhibition.

title: Juggling Balls
description: Pocoyo is very impressed with Elly and Octopus' trick of juggling. He wants to play too. Octopus makes Pocoyo practice lots of different activities but Pocoyo can't see the point because they aren't related to juggling… or so he thinks. In the end Pocoyo becomes the star of the show!

title: Let's Take a Bath
description: Come along and sing with Pocoyo and his friends to Lets Take a Bath!

title: Pocoyo's Little Friend
description: Pocoyo finds a new little friend - a very hungry caterpillar. He watches with amazement as his new friend transforms.

title: Picture This
description: Pocoyo imagines that fish live in different places and draws funny pictures for his friends.

title: Boo!
description: Pocoyo has a new game which he enjoys playing on his friends: BOO! Only some of his friends find Pocoyo's game annoying or frightening. But this only encourages Pocoyo more. He boos poor Pato til he ends up a nervous wreck. Elly sees how scared Pato has become and decides to give Pocoyo a taste of his own medicine. Elly makes Pocoyo jump. At first Pocoyo doesn't like it but ultimately Pato and Pocoyo both realize it can be fun to BOO! and to be BOOED!

title: Poczilla
description: Pocoyo and Pato are playing at being terrifying giant monsters, like the sort of monsters they've seen in their comics. They find a toy city and enjoy being like Godzilla and King Kong. They don't notice that the little toys who live in the city are scared and that they're all running away in terror as Pocoyo and Pato destroy their toy city. The audience tells Pocoyo and Pato to stop. Once Pocoyo and Pato realize what's been going on they repair the damage and make a wonderful funfair for the little toys.

title: Hiccup
description: Pato gets the hiccups. Together Pocoyo, Elly and Loula help him to get rid of them by giving him a surprise.

title: My Best Friend Pato
description: Come along and sing with Pocoyo and his friends to My Best Friend Pato!

title: Pocoyo's Puppet Show
description: Pocoyo finds a puppet theatre and some puppets. Brilliant! Time for him to be a puppeteer. He puts on a show for Caterpillar and Baby Bird. They love it, especially when the puppets do funny things like fall over. They bring Pato and Elly along to watch the show too. When Pocoyo makes fun of Pato and Elly with the puppets, Pato and Elly are nonplussed. They don't think it's so great to laugh at people. Pocoyo realizes that his show has upset his friends. He says sorry and explains he didn't mean it. Everyone makes friends again!

title: The Reflection
description: It's Halloween and everyone is dressing up. Pocoyo, as a wizard, is practicing scaring in front of the mirror and inadvertently makes his Reflection come alive! His Reflection looks just like him but is far more mischievous. The Reflection soon discovers that he can get sweets by scaring people and starts going after all of Pocoyo's friends. They think it's the real Pocoyo, so the Reflection is causing a lot of trouble for poor Pocoyo. Will he be able to clear up the confusion?

title: Dance Off!
description: Pocoyo and Pato stumble upon a disco and Elly is the DJ. Pato gets grooving to a track and Elly thinks he's fantastic. But Pocoyo's not impressed. He has a go and shows his dance. It's wonderful, but then Pato thinks he can do even better. And so it goes on - an impromptu, ever-so-funky dance off! Things get out of hand when Pocoyo is raving and Pato is body-popping so Elly changes the record. She takes to the dance floor and shows the rivals - in an uncannily Britney-esque way - that instead of competing, they can all have fun dancing together! It's much more fun.

title: Umbrella, Umbrella
description: Pocoyo finds an umbrella. He and his friends have great fun playing with the umbrella and trying to work out what it's for. When it starts to rain, Pocoyo - with the help of the children watching - realizes a perfect use for it!

title: Party Pooper
description: Pocoyo is having a party and invites all his friends. But instead of letting his friends have fun, Pocoyo keeps bossing them around. Pato, Elly and Fred soon get fed up and leave the party to play their own way. Left to play on his own, Pocoyo realizes that a party with no guests is no fun at all. Pocoyo invites his friends back to the party and everyone has fun playing together in their own unique and individual ways.

title: Halloween Disco
description: Come along and sing Halloween Disco with Pocoyo and his friends!

title: New on the Planet
description: Pocoyo is scared when a stranger appears in Pocoyoland, but he soon comes to realize that he needn't be scared of this little alien and they become friends.

title: A Mystery Most Puzzling
description: Pocoyo has to follow the clues in a series of photographs to work out who's got the camera.

title: Where's Pocoyo?
description: Pocoyo plays hide and seek with us. Can you find him?

title: Runaway Hat
description: It's a windy day and Pato's hat gets blown away. Pato doesn't like the way he looks without his hat and he's afraid his friends will laugh at him so he hides and won't play. Finally they catch up with him and he tries on a selection of replacement hats, none of which quite fit the bill. When Elly and Pocoyo realize what's wrong they don't understand Pato's reaction. They like the way he looks. Pato comes to see that his friends love him for who he is, not what he looks like and the friends all play happily together.

title: What's In the Box?
description: Pocoyo's new box takes on a life of its own when Loula accidentally crawls underneath it. Eventually with the help of his friends, Pocoyo works out what's - or WHO'S - in the box.

title: Monster Mystery
description: Pocoyo makes a monster mask out of an old box. When he fails to scare Elly and Pato, he kicks the box out of the way in frustration. The box lands on Sleepy Bird who can't get out of it. She flies close to Pocoyo to ask for help but he and his friends are terrified. A chase ensues. Finally Baby Bird works it out. It was Sleepy Bird all along. The friends all have a monster mash party together at the end.

title: Pocoyo's Balloon
description: Pocoyo is taking a walk with his beloved balloon when he is momentarily distracted by Loula and accidentally lets go of the balloon. He is flabbergasted as it drifts away up into the sky, and irreconcilably down in the dumps. Until we help him to realize that some things are more lasting than balloons: friends!

title: Are You Sleeping, Pocoyo?
description: Come along and sing Are you sleeping, Pocoyo? with Pocoyo and his friends!

title: Who's' calling Me Now?
description: Pocoyo finds a box of unusual whistles. To his delight he discovers that each whistle makes a different noise and summons a different one of his chums. Fun until the tables are turned on Pocoyo and there's a whistle that summons him too. Everyone realizes how silly they're being.

title: Superheroes to the Rescue
description: Come along and sing Superheroes to the Rescue with Pocoyo and his friends!

title: Itsy Bitsy Spider
description: Come along and sing with Pocoyo and his friends to Itsy Bitsy Spider!

title: Five Little Ducks
description: Come along and sing with Pocoyo and his friends to the Five Little Ducks song!

title: Band of Friends
description: Pocoyo meets a funny little red shape. At first it teases and hides from him, making him jump and chasing him around. But then it brings along its friends and together they put on a music and dancing show for Pocoyo and his gang.

title: An Alien Christmas Carol
description: The angry Martian hates Christmas since his father disappeared one Christmas Eve and he's decided to use his cannon to ruin Christmas for Pocoyo and his friends. But you never know what life has in store. After all, everyone has a heart.

title: Up Up and Away
description: Our friends are playing with a model airplane which shoots off up into space. They go on an adventure to retrieve the beloved toy, encountering some friendly, bendy aliens along the way.

title: Horse!
description: Pocoyo is flicking though a picture book when he sees something he's never seen before: a horse! He's amazed and obsessed. He desperately wants to have a horse. He searches everywhere and can talk of nothing but horses. His friends try to make a horse for him but Pocoyo rejects their attempt. Elly and Pato were only trying to help and now they're completely exasperated. Pocoyo is going mad - and driving them mad - just talking about horses all the time. Elly starts to cry in despair. Pocoyo realises that he's been driving them crazy and that they were only trying to help. He understands that there are no real horses in Pocoyo's world and he'll just have to do without. He plays with the pretend horse that Elly and Pato made and has loads of fun.

title: Musical Blocks
description: Pocoyo and Pato are having great fun playing with some magical blocks which form towers when music is played. But the fun turns to drama when Pato gets stuck on top of a high tower. How can Pocoyo return his ducky friend back to ground safely?

title: A Little Cloud
description: Pocoyo has an unusual new friend: a lonely little cloud who just wants to play.

title: Five Little Aliens
description: Come along and sing with Pocoyo and his friends to Five little aliens!

title: A colour for everyone
description: Come along and sing with Pocoyo and his friends to The Colors Song!

title: Fussy Duck
description: Pato, fresh from his shower, is determined to keep clean. Pocoyo and Elly have very different ideas, and Pato soon realizes that half the fun of getting clean is getting dirty in the first place!

title: Let's Play in the Forest
description: Come along and sing Lets Play in the Forest with Pocoyo and his friends!

title: Drum Roll Please
description: Pocoyo and his playmates love dancing to the Ball Orchestra's music. When it stops, they try to make their own band. Sleepy Bird's snoring sets the rhythm, and together they all make a wonderful, harmonious din.

title: Fetch Loula Fetch!
description: Pocoyo and Loula are going to the beach, but they keep losing their ball. They learn about colors, shapes and sizes as they meet their friends along the way.

title: The Seed
description: Pocoyo finds a seed. He can't wait for it to grow. He guards it lovingly but can't prevent his friends from taking an interest in the seed too. Sleepy Bird thinks it would make a tasty snack but Pocoyo stops her from munching it just in time. Loula thinks it's a toy to bury and Pato thinks it's an egg. Finally Pocoyo erects a comprehensive security system to protect his seed but Elly accidentally knocks it over. Pocoyo's seed grows into a beautiful flower. But Loula picks it and shakes it. Pocoyo is upset until he realizes - -with our help - that Loula's shaking of the flower has simply made more seeds fall on the ground, and therefore more beautiful flowers have grown.

title: Pocoyo and Nina's Terror Show
description: Pocoyo and Nina put on a puppet show for their friends. They can't wait to see their scared faces... But they don`t get scared at all, the show is hilarious!

title: Noise to My Ears
description: Pocoyo, Elly and Baby Bird have great fun making lots of noise. But what's music to their ears is a real old racket to poor Pato who's trying to have a nap. Pocoyo, Elly and Baby Bird agree to try to be more considerate. But then they find another wonderful way to make music - by bouncing balls. Again, their music wakes up the sleepy duck. Finally Pocoyo and his chums make a cacophony with lots of machines. Pato completely loses his cool. Pocoyo's attempt at a soothing lullaby does nothing to calm the ever-more exhausted quacker. Pato realizes there's no other way round this - he's going to have to conduct them himself. In so doing, he really gets into it and the music gives him lots of energy. He's no longer sleepy and everyone's playing brilliant harmonious music together.

title: Elly's Ballet Class
description: Elly wants to be a prima ballerina with a troupe of other dancers so she tries to teach her friends to dance just like her. But she gets frustrated that they can't do it straight away and is very bossy. Finally everyone dances together in their own special way.

title: Row, Row, Row the Boat
description: Come along and sing Row, Row, Row the Boat with Pocoyo and his friends!

title: If You're Happy And You Know It
description: Come along and sing with Pocoyo and his friends to If you're happy and you know it!

title: Deck the Halls
description: Come along and sing Deck the Halls this Christmas with Pocoyo and his friends!

title: Puppy Love
description: Pocoyo neglects Loula when he finds a toy dog to play with.

title: Rain, Rain, Go Away
description: Come along and sing with Pocoyo and his friends to Rain, Rain, Go away!

title: Table for Fun
description: When Pocoyo and Elly decide to play restaurants, a very hungry Pato becomes their unwilling and unwitting guest. But Pato doesn't understand that it's a game.

title: Halloween Potion
description: It's Halloween and Pocoyo and friends are very excited to go trick-or-treating! Witch Elly is preparing a delicious cream to enjoy before they set out scaring. With full bellies and sure that they are the scariest, they get ready for an evening of fun… but they soon discover that there is a clear winner, it seems that a real monster is loose…! Or maybe not…? Halloween is a magical night and anything is possible!

title: Toothbrush Jazz
description: Come along and sing with Pocoyo and his friends the Toothbrush Jazz song!

title: Pato's Shower
description: Pato has his towel, soap and brush ready for a shower when the phone rings. He goes to answer the phone and when he returns all of his things have disappeared. Pato starts searching and finds that his friends are playing with them. At the end of the episode Pocoyo and Elly realize that it wasn't nice to take Pato's things without permission and help to make Pato's shower unforgettable.

title: Picnic Puzzle
description: Pocoyo and Elly have organized a picnic and they leave Pato in charge of guarding the sandwiches while they get everything ready. Incredibly the sandwiches suddenly start moving around. Pato can't believe his eyes. When Pocoyo and Elly return they are angry with Pato. They think he took the sandwiches himself. They give him one more chance, leaving him in charge of guarding the cake. Once again, amazingly, the cake runs away apparently on its own. Pato is once again berated by Pocoyo and Elly until they see what's going on with their own eyes. Pocoyo investigates further and discovers who it is that's moving the food around: ANTS! Having worked out what's going on, the friends invite the ants along to the picnic and they all have fun together.

title: Baby Bird Sitting
description: When Sleepy Bird has to pop out for a while, she needs someone to look after little Baby Bird. Pato volunteers because he thinks that's going to be a much easier job than tidying up the mess he's made with Pocoyo. Baby Bird, and his chum Caterpillar, run rings round Pato who eventually appeals to Pocoyo for help. Pocoyo thinks he can take care of the situation easily himself, but he similarly is foxed by the little tykes. Finally Pocoyo and Pato work out that in order to get the little ones to do what they want, they are going to need to collaborate. By the time Sleepy Bird returns, Baby Bird and Caterpillar are fast asleep. Little does Sleepy Bird know the chaos that got them to that point!

title: Twinkle Twinkle
description: Elly finds a beautiful star that has fallen out of the night sky. She loves it and wants to keep it for herself. But Pocoyo makes her realize that the star is for everyone to enjoy. Together they put it back where it's meant to be.

title: Mad Mix Machine
description: Pocoyo finds a super duper machine that mixes objects and makes special new toys to play with. But when Pocoyo puts his friends' toys in the machine for fun, he upsets them. Eventually Pocoyo has to put things back to normal and then share his new magic machine with his friends so they can all enjoy it.

title: Bat and Ball
description: It's time for a game of Bat and Ball with Octopus. Everyone wants to have a turn at batting, but the friends learn that you have to wait your turn.

title: The Messy Guest
description: Pocoyo is having a lovely time playing with his friends but little does he realize that he's making a mess and leaving them to clear it all up! When he sees that his friends no longer want to play with him, he comes to understand the importance not only of having fun and making a mess, but of helping and clearing up too.

title: A Surprise for Pocoyo
description: Pocoyo's friends decide to give him a surprise party - simply to show him how much they love him.

title: Duck Stuck
description: Pocoyo finds a strange door. When he opens it, it seems to lead to the sky. Every time Pocoyo opens the door it seems to open up somewhere new.

title: Hickory Dickory Dock
description: Come along and sing Hickory Dickory Dock with Pocoyo and his friends!

title: Lost in Space
description: Pocoyo goes to visit his alien friend who wants to show him around his beautiful planet. Pocoyo and the alien have so much fun with the new things that they see and hear that soon they don't know where they are. At first they both panic but Pocoyo realizes with the narrator's and viewers' help that if he tries to remember the last place he was he'll be sure to find his way home.

title: Egg Surprises (The Jungle)
description: Come along and sing Egg Surprises (the jungle) with Pocoyo and his friends!

title: Numbers
description: Come along and sing with Pocoyo and his friends to the Numbers song!

title: Detective Pocoyo
description: Elly is aghast to realize that her darling doll is missing. Detective Pocoyo decides to help Elly and he looks for clues as to where her doll might be. While Pocoyo goes back to the scene of the crime, Elly finds that she had her doll all along: it wasn't lost at all, she'd simply mislaid it. Elly is too embarrassed to own up and tells Pocoyo she doesn't need her doll anymore. But Detective Pocoyo uncovers the truth and the mystery is solved.

title: Everyone's Present
description: Wow… Presents! One for Pocoyo, one for Elly and one for Pato! How exciting. Pocoyo's present is some string, Pato gets some paper and Elly some sticks. They have fun for a while, each playing with their own present in a bid to prove that it's the best of the bunch. But ultimately the friends get a little bored with their respective gifts. After all, there's only so much you can do with one thing. In a huff, the friends throw their new toys on the floor. And this is when they see the potential of the presents: they can combine them. They put the presents together to make a kite. Wonderful, something they can all play with together.

title: Jingle Bells
description: Come along and sing with Pocoyo and his friends to Jingle Bells during this festive period!

title: Christmas Tree
description: It's Christmas time and Pato wants to decorate a Christmas tree. He can't bring himself to fell an innocent fern, but with a bit of ingenuity and a lot of team work the gang manages to find the perfect tree. Merry Christmas!

title: Pocoyo's Present
description: Pocoyo has a beautifully wrapped up present but he won't open it. Elly is dying to know what's inside. She begs and pleads but when that fails she turns to desperate measures.

title: Colors
description: Pocoyo is building a tower of color blocks. Suddenly the red block speaks. The red block has a yellow friend, a blue friend and a green friend. Pocoyo looks for Pato so that he can see this, but when Pato arrives the "toridoris" have camouflaged themselves as tower blocks. Pocoyo is able to find them again with the help of the children, and looks for Pato once more.

title: Pato Underwater
description: Pato packs his bag of toys and heads off to play with Octopus and Whale underwater. Unfortunately none of his toys work in the sea, and he doesn't like the food so he's all set to head back home. But then Whale shows Pato how fun things can be underwater once you get used to it. Pato has a wonderful time riding on Whale's back, bouncing on sea sponges and playing in a bubble. Finally Pocoyo and Elly arrive too and everyone has a splashy underwater party together.

title: Pocoyolympics
description: Pocoyo, Elly and Pato stage their own version of the olympics - with a funny and very original variety of contests.

title: Whale's Birthday
description: It's Whale's birthday. When all of Whale's presents get spoiled on the way to the party, Pocoyo, Elly and Pato are sad. But Whale is happy just to see them. Friends are what you need for a party!

title: Christmas Far From Home
description: Yanko invites Pocoyo and friends to spend Christmas with him and they accept gladly. However, when they arrive they discover that it's not the ideal plan they had imagined. Everything is made of ice, they slip, it's very cold and the food is disappointing… things are a bit complicated, especially for Pato, who was expecting to spend Christmas next to a chimney with a hot chocolate. But they will soon learn that, in spite of slippery ice, frozen fish and falling into the cold Artic water, the truly important thing is to spend Christmas together.

title: Old McDonald Had a Farm
description: Come along and sing with Pocoyo and his friends to Old McDonald had a Farm!

title: Pocoyo Dance
description: Pocoyo finds a radio. Pato does his funny, funky dance and Elly demonstrates her delicate ballet style. Pocoyo hears a tune he likes and finds his groove. Everyone can dance in their own special way!

title: One elephant was happily swaying
description: Come along and sing with Pocoyo and his friends to One Elephant Balancing!

title: Farewell Friends
description: Pato is leaving: he's packed his bags, he's said goodbye to his room and all his things. He's had one last sniff of his favorite flowers and said goodbye to Caterpillar, Alien, Baby Bird and Sleepy Bird. And there's the plane he's leaving in…! One last chance to say good bye. Good bye Pato!!! Everyone is waving and saying goodbye. Pato gets in the plane. One last wave. It's so sad!!! The plane goes in a circle one super-quick time and then Pato's home again. Hooray. Time for a welcome home party - and for someone else to have a go!

title: Nina had a Farm
description: Come along and sing Nina had a farm with Pocoyo and his friends!

title: Wackily Ever After
description: Pocoyo and his friends are playing dressing up and the narrator decides to tell a story. The traditional fairy tale takes on a decidedly wacky hue as the characters all undercut the conventions with hilarious and surprising results.

title: Wheels on the Bus
description: Come along and sing with Pocoyo and his friends to The Wheels on the Bus!

title: Double Bubble
description: Pocoyo is enjoying blowing bubbles with his bubble maker. Elly wants to play too. They can't agree on who gets to play with it. Finally they realize that the best way to play is to share.

title: Who's on the Phone?
description: Pocoyo finds a phone. He has to work out what it's for, and who's on the other end of the line. It's Elly inviting everyone to a party!

title: Head, Shoulders, Knees and Toes
description: Come along and sing with Pocoyo and his friends to Head, shoulders, knees and toes!

title: The Garden
description: Pato is tending to his garden when Pocoyo arrives. Pocoyo wants to plant a flower so Pato lends him a gardening book so that he can follow the steps to make his plant grow. But Pocoyo doesn't pay attention to the book and, because of this, is only able to grow a ridiculous looking plant. Pato decides to help Pocoyo get his plant to grow and sprout flowers.

title: The Colour of Love
description: Come along and sing The Colour of Love with Pocoyo and his friends!
